166 Streaming Entertainment Fund established under section 7.
167 Section 6. Right to audit financial records pertaining to assessable gross revenues.
168 (a) The Commonwealth shall have the right to conduct an audit or review of the records
169 reasonably related to the sources, amounts and computation of assessable gross revenues derived
170 from, or pertaining to, the sale or provision of streaming entertainment service to individuals and
171 businesses residing in the Commonwealth within the previous three (3) years.
172 (b) Within thirty (30) days of a written request, a streaming entertainment operator shall
173 provide the Department of Revenue with copies of financial records related to the review or audit
9 of 13

174 of assessable gross revenues derived from, or pertaining to, the sale or provision of streaming
175 entertainment services to individuals and businesses residing in the Commonwealth.
176 (c) In the event of an alleged underpayment, the Department of Revenue shall provide the
177 streaming entertainment operator with a written statement indicating the basis for the alleged
178 underpayment. The streaming entertainment operator shall have thirty (30) days from the receipt
179 of a statement regarding an alleged underpayment to provide the Department of Revenue any
180 written objection to the results of any assessable gross revenue review or audit, including any
181 substantiating documentation. Based on this exchange of information, the Department of
182 Revenue shall make a final determination of the underpayment(s), if any, within thirty (30) days
183 of the streaming entertainment operator’s objection and shall provide the operator with written
184 notice of the determination.
185 (d) Any additional assessments due to the Commonwealth as a result of the assessable
186 gross revenue review or audit shall be paid to the Department of Revenue by the streaming
187 entertainment operator within forty-five (45) days from the date of written notification of the
188 final decision. If the assessable gross revenue review or audit shows that amounts have been
189 underpaid, then the streaming entertainment operator shall pay the underpaid amount plus
190 monetary fines equal to ten percent (10%) of the underpayment.
191 (e) A streaming entertainment operator adversely affected by any final action, or failure
192 to act, of the Department of Revenue that is inconsistent with this section may, within thirty (30)
193 days after such action or failure to act, commence an action in any court of competent
194 jurisdiction within the Commonwealth. The court shall hear and decide such action on an
195 expedited basis.
