196 Section 7. Streaming Entertainment Fund
197 (a) There shall be a Streaming Entertainment Fund which shall consist of amounts
198 credited to the fund in accordance with this section. The fund shall be administered by the state
199 treasurer and held in trust exclusively for the purposes of this section. The state treasurer shall be
200 treasurer-custodian of the fund and shall have the custody of its monies and securities.
201 (b) The Streaming Entertainment Fund shall consist of: (i) revenues collected from the
202 assessment imposed by this chapter; (ii) any monetary penalties imposed under this chapter; (iii)
203 revenue from appropriations or other money specifically designated to be credited to the fund;
204 (iv) interest earned on money in the fund; and (v) funds from private sources including, but not
205 limited to, gifts, grants and donations received by the Commonwealth that are specifically
206 designated to be credited to the fund. Amounts credited to the fund shall not be subject to further
207 appropriation and any money remaining in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall not revert to
208 the General Fund. The secretary of the Commonwealth shall annually, not later than December
209 31, report on the activity of the fund to the clerks of the Senate and House of Representatives and
210 the Senate and House Committees on Ways and Means.
211 (c) The Streaming Entertainment Fund shall make bi-annual distributions on March 1 and
212 September 1 of each year. On those dates, the Streaming Entertainment Fund shall allocate, with
213 no remainder left, all monies then held in the Fund according to the yearly distribution table in
214 the annual report of the advisory board under section 4.
215 (d) The Commissioner of Revenue or any official responsible, shall, without further
216 appropriation and upon certification of the Commissioner, distribute all sums allocated under (c)
217 under this section.
11 of 13

218 (e) All sums distributed under subsection (c) of this section shall be deposited in
219 accordance with Section 53F¾ of Chapter 44.
220 (f) All monies collected by the fund shall be used exclusively for the purposes of this
221 chapter and not for any other governmental purpose. No expenditures from the Streaming
222 Entertainment Fund shall be made except to provide funding for: (i) the operating expenses of
223 the fund; (ii) legal and administrative expenses incurred in enforcing the provisions of this
224 chapter; and (iii) legal and administrative expenses incurred in collecting any assessment due
225 under this chapter.
226 (g) All sums appropriated under this chapter shall be expended in a manner reflecting and
227 encouraging a policy of nondiscrimination and equal opportunity.
228 (h) All officials and employees of an agency, board, department, commission or division
229 receiving monies under this chapter shall take affirmative steps to ensure equality of opportunity
230 and nondiscrimination in the internal affairs of state government, as well as in their relations with
231 the public, including those persons and organizations doing business with the Commonwealth.
232 Each agency, board, department, commission or division, in spending appropriated sums and
233 discharging its statutory responsibilities, shall adopt measures to ensure equal opportunity and
234 nondiscrimination in the areas of hiring, promotion, demotion or transfer, recruitment, layoff or
235 termination, rates of compensation, in-service or apprenticeship training programs and all terms
236 and conditions of employment.
237 Section 8. Judicial remedy.
238 (a) In accordance with Section 1 of Chapter 12, the Attorney General is authorized to
239 enforce this chapter. The Attorney General may, within seven (7) years, bring an action to
12 of 13

240 recover any unpaid assessments and monetary penalties, or enjoin the operations of any non-
241 compliant entity, in any court of competent jurisdiction.
242 (b) Any local government, or class thereof, or community media center adversely
243 impacted by the action, or failure to act, of any streaming entertainment operator under this
244 chapter, may, within seven (7) years, bring an action to recover any unpaid assessments and
245 monetary penalties, or enjoin the operations of any non-compliant entity, in any court of
246 competent jurisdiction.
247 SECTION 2. Municipal streaming fund.
248 Section 53 F¾ of Chapter 44 of the General Laws shall be amended by adding at the end
249 thereof the following new section: -
250 “Notwithstanding section 53 or any other general or special law to the contrary, a
251 municipality that accepts this section may establish in the treasury a separate revenue account to
252 be known as the PEG Access and Streaming Entertainment Funds, into which may be deposited
253 funds received in connection with assessments derived from streaming entertainment providers.
254 Monies in the fund shall only be appropriated to support public, educational or governmental
255 access media centers.”
256 SECTION 3. Effective date.
257 This act shall take effect upon its passage.
